SUMMARY:Garden Inspirations: Wonders of Winter
DESCRIPTION:Garden Inspirations: Wonders of Winter \nPlein Air Watercolor Class with Sharon Pitts \nTuesdays\, February 17\, 24\, March 3\, 10\, 1:00 PM – 3:30 PM \nRegistration will open on Tuesday\, January 6.  \nThe focus of our winter series will be the serenity and beauty of winter.  From the white snow intermingled with dark branches to the subtle colors of dried leaves and surprises of berries\, the garden is a treasure of beauty in winter. Each class includes demonstrations and personal attention for each student. Some watercolor experience is desirable. We will work in Van Vleck’s Raymond Family Education Center. A supply list will be sent after registration. \nFee:  4-class Series: $200 Members / $225 General Public  \nPre-Registration is required.  There are no drop-ins for this class. \nDeadline to register is Monday\, February 16. \n \n 
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/garden-inspirations-wonders-of-winter-3/2026-03-10/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2025/07/Cornus-sanguinea-Winter-Flame-4-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
