SUMMARY:MILL at Van Vleck - Pruning
DESCRIPTION:Partner Program with the Montclair Institute for Lifelong Learning \nWinter at Van Vleck \nThursdays\, 1:30 PM- 2:30 PM \nThis class is a Partner Program with the Montclair Institute for Lifelong Learning. To register please visit: http://schedulesplus.com/montclair/kiosk \n3/12 – Pruning \nLet’s talk about why\, where\, when\, and if you should make that cut.  Well-informed pruning decisions affect your plant’s long-term health and beauty.  Please dress for the weather as this class will be held outdoors. \n3/19 – Mini Fairy Gardens \n3/26 – Beginner Birding Class \nSpring dates coming soon
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/mill-at-van-vleck-pruning/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://montclairfoundation.org/content/uploads/2022/12/Garden-How-To-pruning-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
