SUMMARY:MILL at Van Vleck - Beginning Birding Class
DESCRIPTION:Partner Program with the Montclair Institute for Lifelong Learning \nWinter at Van Vleck \nThursdays\, 1:30 PM- 2:30 PM \n3/26 – Beginner Birding Class – Learn how to identify common backyard birds by focusing on their characteristics\, behaviors and feeding habits. This informative session will be with a powerpoint and/or walk depending on the weather. Bring your own binoculars if you have them\, if not some will be provided. \nThis class is a Partner Program with the Montclair Institute for Lifelong Learning. To register please visit: http://schedulesplus.com/montclair/kiosk
URL:https://montclairfoundation.org/event/mill-at-van-vleck-beginning-birding-class/
LOCATION:Van Vleck House & Gardens\, 21 Van Vleck Street\, Montclair\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes,Adults
